{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"3003","heading":"Rules of construction","label":"3003 Rules of construction","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/ptVI/ch176/schA","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3003","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","References in TextThe Federal Rules of Civil Procedure, referred to in subsecs. (c)(8)(A) and (f), are set out in the Appendix to this title.","Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Effective DateSection effective 180 days after , and applicable with respect to certain actions for debts owed the United States pending in court on that effective date, see , set out as a note under .Nov. 29, 1990section 3631 of Pub. L. 101–647section 3001 of this title"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—Terms","label":"a .—Terms","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3003%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3003%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the terms “includes” and “including” are not limiting;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3003%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the term “or” is not exclusive; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3003%2Fa%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the singular includes the plural.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":".—Effect on Rights of the United States","label":"b .—Effect on Rights of the United States","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3003%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3003%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to collect taxes or to collect any other amount collectible in the same manner as a tax;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3003%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to collect any fine, penalty, assessment, restitution, or forfeiture arising in a criminal case;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3003%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to appoint or seek the appointment of a receiver; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/b/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3003%2Fb%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to enforce a security agreement.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":".—Effect on Other Laws","label":"c .—Effect on Other Laws","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3003%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3003%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"title 11;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3003%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"admiralty law;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/c/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3003%2Fc%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":";section 3713 of title 31","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/c/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3003%2Fc%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"section 303 of the Consumer Credit Protection Act ();15 U.S.C. 1673","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/c/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3003%2Fc%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a statute of limitation applicable to a criminal proceeding;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/c/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3003%2Fc%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the common law or statutory rights to set-off or recoupment;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"7","heading":null,"label":"7","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/c/7","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3003%2Fc%2F7","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"any Federal law authorizing, or any inherent authority of a court to provide, injunctive relief;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"8","heading":null,"label":"8","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/c/8","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3003%2Fc%2F8","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/c/8/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/c/8","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3003%2Fc%2F8%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to impose a sanction under the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/c/8/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/c/8","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3003%2Fc%2F8%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to appoint a receiver to effectuate its order; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/c/8/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/c/8","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3003%2Fc%2F8%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to exercise the power of contempt under any Federal law;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"9","heading":null,"label":"9","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/c/9","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3003%2Fc%2F9","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"any law authorizing the United States to obtain partition, or to recover possession, of property in which the United States holds title; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"10","heading":null,"label":"10","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/c/10","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3003%2Fc%2F10","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"any provision of any other chapter of this title, except to the extent such provision is inconsistent with this chapter.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":".—Preemption","label":"d .—Preemption","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3003%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"This chapter shall preempt State law to the extent such law is inconsistent with a provision of this chapter.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"e","heading":".—Effect on Rights of the United States Under Foreign and International Law","label":"e .—Effect on Rights of the United States Under Foreign and International Law","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3003%2Fe","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"This chapter shall not be construed to curtail or limit the rights of the United States under foreign law, under a treaty or an international agreement, or otherwise under international law.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"f","heading":".—Applicability of Federal Rules of Civil Procedure","label":"f .—Applicability of Federal Rules of Civil Procedure","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003/f","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t28/s3003","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft28%2Fs3003%2Ff","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Except as provided otherwise in this chapter, the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure shall apply with respect to actions and proceedings under this chapter.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
